name: ABANGAN WATERFALL
address: F8RC+FWR, Bakbakan, Gianyar, Gianyar Regency, Bali, Indonesia
review 1:
10/10 must come here.
I paid 20,000 IDR ($2 AUS) to see this waterfall, and I was the only tourist there. Three workers were beginning to install the hand rails at the base of the waterfall and were wonderful in taking a break to show me where to sit and stand safely in the waterfall.
The walk down is steep with lots of steps, but well worth it. The river is beautiful and there is a bench to sit at to enjoy the view for a while. Lots of safe places for a swim.
